<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Hidden powers of items show up in the resistance grid when the item isn't *identified* yet. <p>
I know Massimiliano was just working on the resistance grid, so I hope he knows what changed to cause this. 
</p>
<p>
Bandobras: Are they random powers (e.g. of Elven armor, or of randarts), or are they obvious powers, shuch as levitation for boots of levitation, or boots of stability? If the latter is the case, I would ask to change the display of the 'I' command, rather than make these obvious powers hidden in the output of 'C'. I like this in the newest Vanillia. 
</p>
<p>
Neil Stevens: They are powers that are not visible with the I command until the item is *identified*.  Here is a <a href="./BugReport73_2fSpoiler_20example">/Spoiler example</a>. 
</p>
<p>
Bandobras: OK. Perhaps levitation for the boots of stability is not obvious, and the same for your example. But such powers are always the same. After a time I remember they are here and doing *ID* each time, just to make them visible in the "C" screen (and the "I" desription) is tedious. OT: In newest Vanillia all fixed powers are visible after ID. the *ID* is reserved for random powers. I like this. (OTOH I don't like the fact that newest Vanillia shops don't *ID*  items sold to them.) 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


